0J2MgmkZr8","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recbqWBKV8PO9OVix","target":"rec1ZMFtfbEvoGC73","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recbqWBKV8PO9OVix","target":"recBOUtTncbBlfEn9","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recbqWBKV8PO9OVix","target":"rec5xfo0qNCc1wtEI","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recbqWBKV8PO9OVix","target":"recEmcEOTObO9ztFB","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recbqWBKV8PO9OVix","target":"recNwG4bBkZyEhAT4","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recbqWBKV8PO9OVix","target":"rec1cz9Ftp0zE3jJK","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recbqWBKV8PO9OVix","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recOUwQvufaIcojwM","ref":"2Chr.14.1","text":"So Abijah slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city of David: and Asa his son reigned in his stead. In his days the land was quiet ten years.","year":-955},{"id":"recdJiewtStIXSpJ8","ref":"2Chr.14.2","text":"And Asa did that which was good and right in the eyes of the LORD his God:","year":-941},{"id":"rec5QTVFFXlirNnjt","ref":"2Chr.14.3","text":"For he took away the altars of the strange gods, and the high places, and brake down the images, and cut down the groves:","year":-941},{"id":"recwvuxMtSZ3P21kQ","ref":"2Chr.14.4","text":"And commanded Judah to seek the LORD God of their fathers, and to do the law and the commandment.","year":-941},{"id":"recL6Aj8dIvPwprbL","ref":"2Chr.14.5","text":"Also he took away out of all the cities of Judah the high places and the images: and the kingdom was quiet before him.","year":-941},{"id":"recW2yreHsXIHy7sI","ref":"2Chr.14.6","text":"And he built fenced cities in Judah: for the land had rest, and he had no war in those years; because the LORD had given him rest.","year":-941},{"id":"recXsuzos2GtrtTtC","ref":"2Chr.14.7","text":"Therefore he said unto Judah, Let us build these cities, and make about them walls, and towers, gates, and bars, while the land is yet before us; because we have sought the LORD our God, we have sought him, and he hath given us rest on every side. So they built and prospered.","year":-941},{"id":"rece9lR9BLWu6Fw5T","ref":"2Chr.14.8","text":"And Asa had an army of men that bare targets and spears, out of Judah three hundred thousand; and out of Benjamin, that bare shields and drew bows, two hundred and fourscore thousand: all these were mighty men of valour.","year":-941}]}
